Rating: 4
Very very good! I made a few adjustments to the recipe and this will be a keeper for many years to come. I used only 3Tbsp of butter but kept the same amount of molasses and chili powder. Per other reviewers, I doubled the amount of shrimp but kept the same amount of remoulade sauce. I also roasted my shrimp in 2 tsp olive oil plus salt and pepper, coursely chopped them and then tossed them in the sauce while still warm. It took a while to figure out what Westphalian bread is - a very dense German pumpernickel bread. Most specialty grocery stores will carry it; you are looking for a small square package of bread not a big loaf.

